M|vercel-react-best-practices|Comprehensive performance optimization guide for React and Next.js applications, maintained by Vercel. Contains 69 rules across 8 categories, prioritized by impact to guide automated refactoring and c
M|vercel-react-best-practices|Reference these guidelines when:
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- Writing new React components or Next.js pages
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- Implementing data fetching (client or server-side)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- Reviewing code for performance issues
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- Refactoring existing React/Next.js code
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- Optimizing bundle size or load times
M|vercel-react-best-practices|| Priority | Category | Impact | Prefix |
M|vercel-react-best-practices||----------|----------|--------|--------|
M|vercel-react-best-practices|| 1 | Eliminating Waterfalls | CRITICAL | `async-` |
M|vercel-react-best-practices|| 2 | Bundle Size Optimization | CRITICAL | `bundle-` |
M|vercel-react-best-practices|| 3 | Server-Side Performance | HIGH | `server-` |
M|vercel-react-best-practices|| 4 | Client-Side Data Fetching | MEDIUM-HIGH | `client-` |
M|vercel-react-best-practices|| 5 | Re-render Optimization | MEDIUM | `rerender-` |
M|vercel-react-best-practices|| 6 | Rendering Performance | MEDIUM | `rendering-` |
M|vercel-react-best-practices|| 7 | JavaScript Performance | LOW-MEDIUM | `js-` |
M|vercel-react-best-practices|| 8 | Advanced Patterns | LOW | `advanced-` |
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `async-cheap-condition-before-await` - Check cheap sync conditions before awaiting flags or remote values
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `async-defer-await` - Move await into branches where actually used
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `async-parallel` - Use Promise.all() for independent operations
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `async-dependencies` - Use better-all for partial dependencies
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `async-api-routes` - Start promises early, await late in API routes
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `async-suspense-boundaries` - Use Suspense to stream cnt
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `bundle-barrel-imports` - Import directly, avoid barrel files
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `bundle-dynamic-imports` - Use next/dynamic for heavy components
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `bundle-defer-third-party` - Load anl/logging after hydration
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `bundle-conditional` - Load modules only when feature is activated
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `bundle-preload` - Preload on hover/focus for perceived speed
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `server-auth-actions` - Authenticate server actions like API routes
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `server-cache-react` - Use React.cache() for per-request deduplication
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `server-cache-lru` - Use LRU cache for cross-request caching
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `server-dedup-props` - Avoid duplicate serialization in RSC props
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `server-hoist-static-io` - Hoist static I/O (fonts, logos) to module level
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `server-no-shared-module-state` - Avoid module-level mutable request state in RSC/SSR
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `server-serialization` - Minimize data passed to client components
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `server-parallel-fetching` - Restructure components to parallelize fetches
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `server-parallel-nested-fetching` - Chain nested fetches per item in Promise.all
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `server-after-nonblocking` - Use after() for non-blocking operations
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `client-swr-dedup` - Use SWR for automatic request deduplication
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `client-event-listeners` - Deduplicate global event listeners
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `client-passive-event-listeners` - Use passive listeners for scroll
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `client-localstorage-schema` - Version and minimize localStorage data
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `rerender-defer-reads` - Don't subscribe to state only used in callbacks
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `rerender-memo` - Extract expensive work into memoized components
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `rerender-memo-with-default-value` - Hoist default non-primitive props
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `rerender-dependencies` - Use primitive dependencies in effects
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `rerender-derived-state` - Subscribe to derived booleans, not raw values
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `rerender-derived-state-no-effect` - Derive state during render, not effects
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `rerender-functional-setstate` - Use functional setState for stable callbacks
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `rerender-lazy-state-init` - Pass function to useState for expensive values
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `rerender-simple-expression-in-memo` - Avoid memo for simple primitives
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `rerender-split-combined-hooks` - Split hooks with independent dependencies
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `rerender-move-effect-to-event` - Put interaction logic in event handlers
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `rerender-transitions` - Use startTransition for non-urgent updates
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `rerender-use-deferred-value` - Defer expensive renders to keep input responsive
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `rerender-use-ref-transient-values` - Use refs for transient frequent values
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `rerender-no-inline-components` - Don't define components inside components
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `rendering-animate-svg-wrapper` - Animate div wrapper, not SVG element
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `rendering-cnt-visibility` - Use cnt-visibility for long lists
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `rendering-hoist-jsx` - Extract static JSX outside components
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `rendering-svg-precision` - Reduce SVG coordinate precision
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `rendering-hydration-no-flicker` - Use inline script for client-only data
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `rendering-hydration-suppress-warning` - Suppress expected mismatches
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `rendering-activity` - Use Activity component for show/hide
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `rendering-conditional-render` - Use ternary, not && for conditionals
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `rendering-usetransition-loading` - Prefer useTransition for loading state
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `rendering-resource-hints` - Use React DOM resource hints for preloading
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `rendering-script-defer-async` - Use defer or async on script tags
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `js-batch-dom-css` - Group CSS changes via classes or cssText
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `js-index-maps` - Build Map for repeated lookups
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `js-cache-property-access` - Cache object properties in loops
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `js-cache-function-results` - Cache function results in module-level Map
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `js-cache-storage` - Cache localStorage/sessionStorage reads
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `js-combine-iterations` - Combine multiple filter/map into one loop
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `js-length-check-first` - Check array length before expensive comparison
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `js-early-exit` - Return early from functions
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `js-hoist-regexp` - Hoist RegExp creation outside loops
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `js-min-max-loop` - Use loop for min/max instead of sort
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `js-set-map-lookups` - Use Set/Map for O(1) lookups
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `js-tosorted-immutable` - Use toSorted() for immutability
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `js-flatmap-filter` - Use flatMap to map and filter in one pass
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `js-request-idle-callback` - Defer non-critical work to browser idle time
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `advanced-effect-event-deps` - Don't put `useEffectEvent` results in effect deps
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `advanced-event-handler-refs` - Store event handlers in refs
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `advanced-init-once` - Initialize app once per app load
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `advanced-use-latest` - useLatest for stable callback refs
